[src:javascript/api-fs-p01] If the accessibility check is successful, the promise is fulfilled with no value.
[src:javascript/api-fs-p01] If any of the accessibility checks fail, the promise is rejected with an `<Error>` object.
[src:javascript/api-fs-p01] Using `fsPromises.access()` to check for the accessibility of a file before calling `fsPromises.open()` is not recommended.
[src:javascript/api-fs-p01] Doing so introduces a race condition, since other processes may change the file's state between the two calls.
[src:javascript/api-fs-p01] Instead, user code should open/read/write the file directly and handle the error raised if the file is not accessible.
[src:javascript/api-fs-p01] Asynchronously append data to a file, creating the file if it does not yet exist.
