[src:javascript/api-fs-p01] Change the file system timestamps of the object referenced by `path`.
[src:javascript/api-fs-p01] The `atime` and `mtime` arguments follow these rules: Values can be either numbers representing Unix epoch time, `Date`s, or a numeric string like `'123456789.0'`.
[src:javascript/api-fs-p01] If the value can not be converted to a number, or is `NaN`, `Infinity`, or `-Infinity`, an `Error` will be thrown.
[src:javascript/api-fs-p01] On most platforms, `'rename'` is emitted whenever a filename appears or disappears in the directory.
