[src:javascript/api-fs-p01] The callback APIs perform all operations asynchronously, without blocking the event loop, then invoke a callback function upon completion or error.
[src:javascript/api-fs-p01] The callback APIs use the underlying Node.js threadpool to perform file system operations off the event loop thread.
[src:javascript/api-fs-p01] The final argument, `callback`, is a callback function that is invoked with a possible error argument.
[src:javascript/api-fs-p01] If any of the accessibility checks fail, the error argument will be an `Error` object.
